statements: SELECT * FROM user_access_logs ORDER BY access_timestamp DESC LIMIT 10

SELECT log_id, access_timestamp FROM user_access_logs
SELECT * FROM user_access_logs ORDER BY access_timestamp DESC LIMIT 10
SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) as total_logs FROM user_access_logs GROUP BY user_id ORDER BY total_logs DESC
SELECT user_id, accessed_resource, access_timestamp FROM user_access_logs WHERE user_id = 123 AND accessed_resource LIKE '%document%' ORDER BY access_timestamp ASC LIMIT 5
SELECT DISTINCT user_id FROM user_access_logs WHERE access_timestamp BETWEEN '2021-01-01' AND '2021-12-31'
SELECT user_id, COUNT(DISTINCT accessed_resource) as distinct_resources FROM user_access_logs GROUP BY user_id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT accessed_resource) >= 3 ORDER BY distinct_resources DESC

SELECT u.user_id, r.role_name, p.permission_name FROM user_roles r JOIN user_role_mapping rm ON r.role_id = rm.role_id JOIN user_permissions p ON rm.role_id = p.role_id JOIN user_access_logs ual ON ual.user_id = rm.user_id WHERE ual.access_type = 'logout';

SELECT DISTINCT r.role_name, p.permission_name FROM user_roles r JOIN role_permission_mapping rp ON r.role_id = rp.role_id JOIN user_permissions p ON rp.permission_id = p.permission_id WHERE r.role_name = 'admin';
